Well this is sortof the "implement character classes" bit of implementing that.

Notably, all of the operators for generating regular languages more or less exist. You can define:

```python
@defines_strategy
def cat(*args):
    return tuples(*args).map(''.join)

@defines_strategy
def empty():
   return just(u'')

@defines_strategy
def plus(strategy):
   return lists(strategy, min_size=1).map(''.join)

@defines_strategy
def star(strategy):
   return lists(strategy).map(''.join)
```

And you're done! Hypothesis text strategies are closed under all the regular language operators. Attaching a regex parser to that is possible if you want but doesn't seem super useful.

