Hi @briang1  I am, though could you try one last thing first?

In your `tinymce_setup.js` (if you're using the one bundled with grappelli, copy it to a static dir in your project), change `mode` in the `tinyMCE.init()` call to `'none'` and add the following javascript somewhere:

```javascript
(function($) {
    $(document).ready(function() {
        $('.djn-inline-form:not(.grp-empty-form) textarea').each(function() {
            tinyMCE.execCommand("mceAddControl", true, this.id);
        });
    });
})(django.jQuery || window.jQuery);
```

To explain the thinking for the above: I believe the _real_ issue here is that tinymce is registering on all textareas indiscriminately, including those in the "empty forms," which are hidden forms that get cloned to become inlines added via javascript. If you prevent tinymce from adding controls to these textareas in the first place, you shouldn't need to remove them when adding an inline.

