@lkraider The only version of this that worked for me to pass context into a custom type with 2.0.1 was:

obj.to_primitive(context={'app_data':{'key': 'val'}})

By comparison:

obj.app_data = {'key': 'val'}
obj.to_primitive()

leaves context.app_data empty.

