@anisjonischkeit I think this is issue is happening because there is a semantic difference in the GraphQL specification between an argument that is `null` vs one that is not defined: http://facebook.github.io/graphql/October2016/#sec-Null-Value That is why when `name` is not defined, in your example, it is not passed to the `mutate` method at all.

The way to work around that is to use kwargs:

```python
class DoMutation(graphene.Mutation):
    class Arguments:
        name = graphene.String()

    ok = graphene.Boolean()

    def mutate(self, info, **args):
		name = args.get('name', None)
        # mutate
        return DoMutation(ok=True)
```

I don't think changing the default value of the `required` attribute is a good idea since it will be diverging from the GraphQL specification.

